In a speech at Arlington National Cemetery, President Biden honored veterans and their families on Veterans Day. He spoke about the sacrifices made by veterans throughout history and the importance of supporting them. The President also highlighted the progress made in providing benefits and care for veterans, including the passage of the PACT Act to help those exposed to toxins and burn pits. He emphasized the need to continue working towards improving services and ensuring that no veteran is denied the honor they earned. The President concluded by urging unity and collective action to keep the light of liberty shining for future generations.